@node System "mrjQuote : System Requirements"
@{par}@{b}System Requirements@{ub}
@{par}~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{par}  An Amiga! (Surprise, surprise)
@{par}  Workbench 2 or better is required for anything other than just printing a
quote to the CLI (or generating a signature) and then exiting.
@{par}  mrjQuote has not been tested with lower OS versions - chances are it may not
work at all, or even crash. If it is 1.3 compatable at all, then that's more
by accident than design - 1.3 is obselete now.
@{par}  A Harddisk is preferable if you're going to be using the program as a
commodity, with ARexx or for large or numerous Quote files, and will certainly
speed things up immesurably.
@{par}  Tested on an A1200/020/28MHz with 4 megs Fast RAM and a hard disk.
@{par}
@endnode
@node Tech "mrjQuote : Technical Details"
@{par}@{b}Technical Details@{ub}
@{par}~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{par}  mrjQuote consists of over 900 lines of code using Blitz Basic 2.1 by Acid
Software. Compile time is a little over 4 seconds on an 020/28. Feel free to
compile your own version if there are any things you want to change -
conditional compilation is set up to easily remove some of the major features
if you don't want them (thus reducing executable size), although this is done
fairly simply and ther are doubtless other bits of code which could be removed
as well. Details, and a list of 3rd party libraries required for compilation
are included at the top of the code.
@{par}  Remember that you are @{b}NOT@{ub} permitted to @{"distribute" link Distribution} altered code or
executables. However, if you have implemented a feature that you think others
might find useful, feel free to get into contact with @{"me" link Author}.
@{par}
@endnode
