@{par}
@endnode
@node Distribution "mrjQuote : Distribution"
@{par}@{b}Distribution@{ub}
@{par}~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{par}  This software is Freeware. Feel free to give it to your friends, force it on
your enemies or feed it to your dog (but only if you've first transferred it
to some suitably edible media). The software should only be distributed as is,
complete with source code, scripts, images and documentation. If space is very
tight, the quotes may be omitted. You may not distribute modified versions of
the executable, source or scripts under any circumstances. If you have any
improved code, feel free to contact me about including it in the next release
- you'll get full credit. Additional scripts and QuoteLists are also welcome.
If you use this program regularly, then please think about 'registering'. A
lot of work has gone into this project and while some of it is for my benefit,
some (for example this documentation) is soley to the benefit of others. I've
no way (or desire) to enforce the rules below, but if you don't even bother to
boost my ego by telling me how great you thing this program is, then don't be
surprised if my associates come along to slice'n'dice you...
@{par}
@{par}@{b}If you use this program regularly, you are morally obligated to:@{ub}
@{par}
@{par}@{b}1)@{ub} Watch @{"Babylon 5" link Babylon5} (You won't regret it)
@{par}@{b}2)@{ub} Buy Directory Opus 5.5 (you won't regret that either)
@{par}@{b}3)@{ub} Send @{"me" link Author} a gift. At the very least an email or SnailMail telling me how
much you like/hate it (and pointing out any bugs you've found, or suggesting
some improvements), but feel free to send something else as well: money,
chocolate, programs you've written (preferably registered versions if they're
shareware) or whatever else takes your fancy. If you send me an email address,
I'll try to keep you informed of any updates or other programs that I write.
Remember that requests for improvements are more likely to be carried out if
they come with some form of gift.
@{par}
@{par}  This archive may be placed on Aminet, and any similar free-access FTP sites,
BBSs, Aminet CDs and Fred Fish's AmigaLibrary. It can be included in other
public domain collections, provided that charges made are minimal. (I would
suggest no more than Ł2 per floppy, Ł20 per CD) You can also include it on the
coverdisk/CD of a magazine provided that you send me a copy of the mag.
@{par}
@{par}The latest version of this, and any other programs I have written, can be
found on my World Wide Web site at:
@{par}http://users.ox.ac.uk/~kebl0206/mrjsw/
@{par}
@endnode
@node Disclaimer "mrjQuote : Disclaimer"
@{par}@{b}Disclaimer@{ub}
@{par}~~~~~~~~~~
@{par}YOU USE THIS SOFTWARE ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN RISK. I PROVIDE NO GUARANTEE THAT
IT WILL WORK FULLY (OR EVEN AT ALL) ON YOUR COMPUTER. I HEREBY REJECT ANY
RESPONSIBILITY OR LIABILITY FOR ANY DAMAGE THAT USE OF THIS PROGRAM MAY CAUSE
TO YOUR COMPUTER, DATA, FINANCES, SELF, SANITY OR ANY OTHER PART OF THE
UNIVERSE (OR ELSEWHERE), REAL OR IMAGINED.
@{par}
@{par}SO THERE.
@{par}
@endnode
@node History "mrjQuote : History and Future"
@{par}@{b}History and Future@{ub}
@{par}~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{par}@{b}v1.00@{ub} First release. A bit crappy.
@{par}@{b}v1.10@{ub} A whole slew of unreleased versions, mainly because I was more
@{par} ...   interested in adding new features than rewriting the docs etc...
@{par}@{b}v1.60@{ub} (plus I didn't keep track of where features were added. Grrrr.)
@{par}@{b}v2.00@{ub} Second release with millions of new and useful functions, including
@{"commodities support" link Commodity} and @{"configuration window" link Configuration}.
@{par}@{b}v2.01@{ub} Something changed. I think.
@{par}@{b}v2.02@{ub} Fixed to work with any size window title font.
@{par}@{b}v2.03@{ub} @{"About requester" link A_about} added and default hotkeys changed.
@{par}@{b}v2.04@{ub} Improved @{"quote file list format" link More}, improved parsing of files and CLI
arguments plus use of mrjQuote as default tool for icons on quote files. Can
read files of quotes directly.
@{par}@{b}v2.05@{ub} @{"Font used by GUI" link A_font} can now be changed.
@{par}@{b}v2.10@{ub} GUI window is now resizable, 'Test' tests new font also.
@{par}@{b}v2.11@{ub} Basic @{"ARexx port" link ARexx} added.
@{par}@{b}v2.12@{ub} Window resizing and font testing speeded up.
@{par}@{b}v2.13@{ub} First test of @{".signature generation" link Sigs}.
@{par}@{b}v2.14@{ub} Signature generation now fully integrated with configuration.
@{par}@{b}v2.15@{ub} Minor bugfixes and cleanups, ARexx port expanded.
@{par}@{b}v2.16@{ub} @{"Load..." link A_load} and @{"Save..." link A_saveas} preferences.
@{par}@{b}v2.17@{ub} Bug in ARexx port fixed, @{"episode list" link Babylon5} added to documentation.
@{par}@{b}v2.20@{ub} Third release.
@{par}@{b}v2.21@{ub} More @{"command-line functionality" link usage} added.
@{par}@{b}v2.22@{ub} Code largely rewritten with a much clearer format and no GOSUBs.
Executable slightly smaller, memory usage should be lower. More functionality
to .signature generation.
@{par}@{b}v2.23@{ub} ARexx port rewritten, extra paramaters, @{"Get/Set" link A_getset} commands.
@{par}@{b}v2.24@{ub} Menus expanded, @{"ARexx macro" link A_macro} feature added.
@{par}@{b}v2.25@{ub} Extra GUI functionality, another CLI option, more code optimisations.
@{par}@{b}v2.26@{ub} Yet more GUI functionality, several bugs squished, workaround for
ARexx RESULT failure added, runtime error debugging removed (saves 10x as much
executable size as optimisations...)
@{par}@{b}v2.27@{ub} Menus and gadgets tidied up, this documentation finally brought up to
date, various images and ARexx scripts produced.
@{par}@{b}v2.28@{ub} Quote extracting routine improved - faster if a file of quotes is
referenced directly, recursive quotelists possible. Constants used in source
code for increased readability.
@{par}@{b}v2.29@{ub} Minor bugs fixed, ARexx 'Set' can now pop up a file requester if
required, some commenting of source added, this documentation greatly
expanded, @{"conditional compilation" link Tech} supported.
@{par}@{b}v2.30@{ub} Fourth Release, small bug in quote parsing fixed.
@{par}
@{par}@{b}Future possibilities:@{ub}
@{par}
@{par}@{b}Use of ReqTools:@{ub} Nicer file and font requesters, better other requesters
(unless you're using Arq). Requesters can be asynchronous, meaning that the
the program isn't locked when a requester opens.
@{par}@{b}AppIcon/Window/Menu support:@{ub} I reckon that this is a bit too gimmicky, but
if anyone desparately wants it, it can be done.
@{par}@{b}Anything else that you suggest to @{"me...." link Author}@{ub}
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_about "mrjQuote: Actions : About mrjQuote"
@{par}@{" Menu     " link Configuration} Project / About
@{par}@{" Keyboard " link Configuration} Right-Amiga A
@{par}
@{par}  Pop up an about requester. In addition to the usual stuff, this will also
detail mrjQuote's commodity name and ARexx port name (if appropriate) and if
ARexx macros are available.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_cancel "mrjQuote: Actions : Cancel configuration changes"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} Cancel
@{par}@{" Menu     " link Configuration} Preferences / Cancel
@{par}@{" Keyboard " link Configuration} Right-Amiga C
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Cancel
@{par}
@{par}  Reset the configuration to what it was before the last time the
configuration window was opened and close the configuration window if it is
still open.
@{par}Equivalent to: @{" Load T:mrjQuote.prefs " link A_load}
@{par}               @{" Close                 " link A_close}
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_close "mrjQuote: Actions : Close configuration window"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} Window close-gadget
@{par}@{" Exchange " link Commodity} Hide Interface
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Close
@{par}
@{par}  Close the configuration window if it is open. No files will be loaded or
saved.
@{par}See also: @{" Use    " link A_use}
@{par}          @{" Cancel " link A_cancel}
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_font "mrjQuote: Actions : Set GUI font"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} GUI Font
@{par}
@{par}  Pops up a requester alowing you to change the font used in the configuration
window's gadgets and menus. The font may be proportional, and size is limited
only by screen height. The configuration window will be redrawn if it is open.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_getset "mrjQuote: Actions : Get / Set configuration variable"
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Get <Variable>
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Set <Variable> [<FileName>]
@{par}
@{par}  Store one of the configuration variables in T:mrjQuote where it can be read
by an ARexx script (supposed to be returned in RESULT, but that doesn't work),
or set one of the @{"configuration" link Configuration} variables to a given filename (including full
path, will pop up a file requester if no file supplied). The possible
variables are:
@{par}
@{par}@{" QuoteList " link A_qlist} @{" SigList " link A_slist} @{" SigFile " link A_sfile} @{" SigPre " link A_spre} @{" SigPost " link A_spre}
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_load "mrjQuote: Actions : Load configuration"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} Load
@{par}@{" Menu     " link Configuration} Preferences / Load
@{par}@{" Keyboard " link Configuration} Right-Amiga L
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Load [<PrefsFile>]
@{par}
@{par}  Load the configuration from a file. This may be supplied (with full path)
via ARexx, in any other case a file-requester will be popped up. All current
settings will be overwritten, and the configuration window will be redrawn if
it is open.
@{par}See also: @{" SaveAs " link A_saveas}
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_macro "mrjQuote: Actions : Execute ARexx Macro"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} Rexx Name
@{par}@{" Menu     " link Configuration} Project / Macro
@{par}@{" Keyboard " link Configuration} Right-Amiga M
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Macro [<MacroName>]
@{par}
@{par}  Execute an mrjQuote ARexx macro. This may be supplied (with full path) via
ARexx, in any other case a file-requester will be popped up. This ARexx script
will then be executed with mrjQuote as the current host port.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_open "mrjQuote: Actions : Open configuration window"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} Configure
@{par}@{" Exchange " link Commodity} Show Interface
@{par}@{" Hotkey   " link Commodity} Configuration Key - Default: Right-Alt Control Q
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Open
@{par}
@{par}  Open or refresh the configuration window. If the window is not open, then
the current configuration will be @{"saved" link A_saveas} in the file T:mrjQuote.prefs before
it is opened.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_qlist "mrjQuote: Actions : Set QuoteList file"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} QuoteList
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} @{" Get / Set " link A_getset} QuoteList [<FileName>]
@{par}
@{par}  Pops up a requester allowing you to set the default QuoteList.  A file may
be specified directly when using ARexx.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_quit "mrjQuote: Actions : Quit mrjQuote"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} Quit
@{par}@{" Menu     " link Configuration} Project / Quit
@{par}@{" Keyboard " link Configuration} Right-Amiga Q
@{par}@{" Exchange " link Commodity} Remove
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Quit
@{par}
@{par}  Quit mrjQuote. No warning will be given.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_quote "mrjQuote: Actions : Pop up a quote"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} Quote
@{par}@{" Menu     " link Configuration} Project / Quote
@{par}@{" Keyboard " link Configuration} Right-Amiga O
@{par}@{" Hotkey   " link Commodity} Quote Key - Default: Left-Alt Control Q
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Quote [<QuouteList>]
@{par}
@{par}  Pop up a random quote in a requester. With ARexx, you can optionally supply
the full path and filename of a QuoteList to be used in place of the currently
configured one.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_reply "mrjQuote: Actions : Generate quote in a file"
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Reply [<QuoteFile>]
@{par}
@{par}  Generate a random quote and store it in the file T:mrjQuote (supposed to be
returned in RESULT, but this doesn't work). You can optionally supply the full
path and filename of a QuoteList to be used in place of the currently
configured one.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_save "mrjQuote: Actions : Save current configuration"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} Save
@{par}@{" Menu     " link Configuration} Preferences / Save
@{par}@{" Keyboard " link Configuration} Right-Amiga S
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Save
@{par}
@{par}  Save the current configuration to ENVARC:mrjsw/Quote and ENV:mrjsw/Quote
and close the configuration window if it is open.
@{par}Equivalent to: @{" SaveAs ENVARC:mrjsw/Quote " link A_saveas}
@{par}               @{" Use                       " link A_use}
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_saveas "mrjQuote: Actions : Save current configuration as..."
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} Save As
@{par}@{" Menu     " link Configuration} Preferences / Save As
@{par}@{" Keyboard " link Configuration} Right-Amiga V
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} SaveAs [<PrefsFile>]
@{par}
@{par}  Save the current configuration to a file. This may be supplied (with full
path) via ARexx, in any other case a file-requester will be popped up.
@{par}See also: @{" Load " link A_load}
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_sfile "mrjQuote: Actions : Set signature file"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} .sig file
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} @{" Get / Set " link A_getset} SigFile [<FileName>]
@{par}
@{par}  Pops up a requester allowing you to set the location of your signature file.
A file may be specified directly when using ARexx.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_sig "mrjQuote: Actions : Generate signature"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} Signature
@{par}@{" Menu     " link Configuration} Project / Signature
@{par}@{" Keyboard " link Configuration} Right-Amiga I
@{par}@{" Hotkey   " link Commodity} Signature Key - Default: Alt Control S
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Sig [<SigList>]
@{par}
@{par}  Generate a random signature. The .sig pre file will be prepended to the
random quote and the .sig post file appended.  With ARexx, you can optionally
supply the full path and filename of a QuoteList to be used in place of the
currently configured one.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_slist "mrjQuote: Actions : Set signature list"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} SigList
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} @{" Get / Set " link A_getset} SigList [<FileName>]
@{par}
@{par}  Pops up a requester allowing you to set the default QuoteList. A file may be
specified directly when using ARexx.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_spost "mrjQuote: Actions : Set signature post"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} .sig post
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} @{" Get / Set " link A_getset} SigPost [<FileName>]
@{par}
@{par}  Allows you to select a file which will (if it exists) be appended to any
random signature generated. A file may be specified directly when using ARexx.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_spre "mrjQuote: Actions : Set signature pre"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} .sig pre
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} @{" Get / Set " link A_getset} SigPre [<FileName>]
@{par}
@{par}  Allows you to select a file which will (if it exists) be prepended to any
random signature generated. A file may be specified directly when using ARexx.
@{par}
@endnode
@node A_use "mrjQuote: Actions : Use current configuration"
@{par}@{" Gadget   " link Configuration} Use
@{par}@{" Menu     " link Configuration} Preferences / Use
@{par}@{" Keyboard " link Configuration} Right-Amiga U
@{par}@{" ARexx    " link ARexx} Use
@{par}
@{par}  Save the current configuration to ENV:mrjsw/Quote and close the
configuration window if it is open.
@{par}Equivalent to: @{" SaveAs ENV:mrjsw/Quote " link A_saveas}
@{par}               @{" Close                  " link A_close}
@{par}
@endnode
@node Rexx "mrjQuote : ARexx : mrjQuote.rexx"
@{par}@{b}mrjQuote.rexx@{ub}
@{par}~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{par}  This @{"ARexx" link ARexx} script is intended for use instead of loading Quote directly from
the CLI. It offers several advantages: the Quote executable will not be run
again if a version with an ARexx port is already running, and it is possible
to install mrjQuote as a commodity or with ARexx an producing a quote to the
CLI. You can also tell an already running copy of mrjQuote to open its
configuration window or quit. For more details, see the documentation
contained within the @{"script itself" link ARexx/mrjQuote.rexx/Main}.
@{par}
@endnode
@node DOpus5 "mrjQuote : ARexx : mrjQuote.dopus5"
@{par}@{b}mrjQuote.dopus5@{ub}
@{par}~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{par}  This is an @{"ARexx" link ARexx} module for Directory Opus 5.5 which has similar functions
to the @{"mrjQuote.rexx" link Rexx} script. It creates two internal Opus commands which can
be used to control mrjQuote, and can optionaly load mrjQuote when DOpus is
started. An added bonus is the ability to pop up quotes using Opus 5
requesters rather than directly from mrjQuote - thus avoiding the problem of
locking up mrjQuote. For further details, see the documentation contained
within @{"the script itself" link ARexx/mrjQuote.dopus5/Main}.
@{par}
@endnode
@node Editor "mrjQuote : ARexx : Scripts for editors"
@{par}@{b}Scripts for Editors@{ub}
@{par}~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{par}  The purpose of these @{"ARexx" link ARexx} scripts is to aid the composition of emails and
news articles. They can be used to indent quoted text and also to create and
append a random signature. The exact functionality will depend on particular
editors. Read the documentation at the top of a script for exact usage
details. Scripts currently supplied are:
@{par}
@{par} @{" IndentAddSig.ged " link ARexx/IndentAddSig.ged/Main} - For use with GoldEd 4
@{par} @{" IndentAddSig.bed " link ARexx/IndentAddSig.bed/Main} - For use with Blacks Editor
@{par}
@{par}  Feel free to develop versions of this script for your favourite editor (and
send a copy to me to include in the next release). Alternatively, if you want
a version for a (freely available) editor not yet supported, and don't want to
do the ARexx programming yourself, then get in contact with me, and I'll see
what I can do. Remember that it's a scientifically proven fact that chocolate
greatly aids the creation of ARexx scripts (hint, hint).
@{par}
@endnode
@node Pilot "mrjQuote : Babylon 5 : The Gathering"
@TOC Babylon5
@{par}@{b}Pilot Movie - "The Gathering"@{ub}
@{par}~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{par}I was there at the dawn of the Third Age of Mankind. It began in the Earth
year 2257 with the founding of the last of the Babylon stations, located deep
in neutral space. It was a port of call for refugees, smugglers, businessmen,
diplomats and travelers from a hundred worlds. It could be a dangerous place,
but we accepted the risk because Babylon 5 was our last, best hope for peace.
Under the leadership of its final commander, Babylon 5 was a dream given form,
a dream of a galaxy without war, when species from different worlds could live
side-by-side in mutual respect, a dream that was endangered as never before by
the arrival of one man on a mission of destruction. Babylon 5 was the last of
the Babylon stations. This is its story. 
-- Ambassador Londo Mollari
@{par}
@{par} @{" 000.txt " link Babylon5/Pilot/000.txt/Main} The Gathering
@{par}
@endnode
@node Season1 "mrjQuote : Babylon 5 : Signs and Portents"
@TOC Babylon5
@{par}@{b}Season One - "Signs and Portents"@{ub}
@{par}~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{par}It was the Dawn of the Third Age of Mankind, ten years after the Earth-Minbari
War. The Babylon Project was a dream given form. Its goal: to prevent another
war by creating a place where humans and aliens could work out their
differences peacefully. It's a port of call, home away from home for
diplomats, hustlers, entrepreneurs and wanderers. Humans and aliens wrapped in
two million, five hundred thousand tons of spinning metal...all alone in the
night. It can be a dangerous place, but it's our last, best hope for peace.
This is the story of the last of the Babylon stations. The year is 2258. The
name of the place...is Babylon 5. 
-- Commander Jeffery Sinclair
@{par}
@{par} @{" 001.txt " link Babylon5/Season1/001.txt/Main} Midnight on the Firing Line
@{par} @{" 002.txt " link Babylon5/Season1/002.txt/Main} Soul Hunter
